{
  "text": ". The rate of the respiratory burst of neutrophils after being co-cultured with LPS-primed MSCs reduced compared to the respiratory burst of neutrophils by them self [CITATION_1] . Generally, these findings might provide a new insight into understanding the anti-inflammatory and immunomodulatory effects of nicotine and caffeine.",
